To convert \(-\tfrac{5\pi}{12}\) radians to degrees, multiply by \(\tfrac{180^\circ}{\pi}\):

\[
-\frac{5\pi}{12}\times\frac{180^\circ}{\pi}
=-\frac{5\cdot180^\circ}{12}
=-\frac{900^\circ}{12}
=-75^\circ.
\]

So \(-\tfrac{5\pi}{12}\) rad = \(-75^\circ\) (equivalently \(285^\circ\) if you prefer a positive coterminal angle).
